Sentencas: Sintering of Ni particles in Ni infiltrated porous YSZ anodes and decrease in triple phase boundary is the reason for performance loss in SOFC.
Titulo: Ni infiltrated YSZ anode stabilization by inducing strong metal support interaction between nickel and titania in solid oxide fuel cell under accelerated testing

Sentencas: In the present work, the idea of strong metal support interaction (SMSI) has been used to prevent the sintering of Ni particles by introducing TiO2 as support with Ni catalyst.
Titulo: Ni infiltrated YSZ anode stabilization by inducing strong metal support interaction between nickel and titania in solid oxide fuel cell under accelerated testing

Sentencas: Electrical conductivity variation of porous YSZ matrix impregnated with Ni and Ni/TiO2 have been investigated.
Titulo: Ni infiltrated YSZ anode stabilization by inducing strong metal support interaction between nickel and titania in solid oxide fuel cell under accelerated testing

Sentencas: Single button cells (anode supported) with and without TiO2 impregnated Ni-YSZ anode were fabricated and characterized through current-voltage measurement at different loads.
Titulo: Ni infiltrated YSZ anode stabilization by inducing strong metal support interaction between nickel and titania in solid oxide fuel cell under accelerated testing

Sentencas: It is shown that the conductivity of porous Ni-YSZ anode and the performance of SOFC button cell with the same anode decreased with the increase in temperature and redox cycling at different time intervals.
Titulo: Ni infiltrated YSZ anode stabilization by inducing strong metal support interaction between nickel and titania in solid oxide fuel cell under accelerated testing

Sentencas: The power density of 12% Ni-YSZ anode was 116 mW/cm(2) and it increased to 180 mW/cm(2) for 12% Ni-4% TiO2-YSZ based anodes at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Ni infiltrated YSZ anode stabilization by inducing strong metal support interaction between nickel and titania in solid oxide fuel cell under accelerated testing

Sentencas: This increase was interpreted by strong attachment of Ni particles on TiO2 preventing Ni coarsening during prolonged reduction in H-2 at 800 degrees C as observed by SEM.
Titulo: Ni infiltrated YSZ anode stabilization by inducing strong metal support interaction between nickel and titania in solid oxide fuel cell under accelerated testing

Sentencas: The power density increased with further increase in Ni loading and it reached to 400 mW/cm(2) for 16% Ni-4% TiO2-YSZ based anodes.
Titulo: Ni infiltrated YSZ anode stabilization by inducing strong metal support interaction between nickel and titania in solid oxide fuel cell under accelerated testing

Sentencas: The performance increases with addition of TiO2 support in Ni-YSZ based anodes corroborates with the impedance spectroscopy analyses.
Titulo: Ni infiltrated YSZ anode stabilization by inducing strong metal support interaction between nickel and titania in solid oxide fuel cell under accelerated testing
